### 🟠 MEDIUM — A05: Security Misconfiguration — Missing Security Headers

**Issue:** No security-related HTTP headers are set. This exposes users to clickjacking, MIME-sniffing, and XSS attacks.

**Fix:** Install and use `helmet`:

```bash
npm install helmet
```

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');

// Apply early, before all routes
app.use(helmet());
// This automatically sets:
// X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
// X-Frame-Options: DENY
// Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS)
// Content-Security-Policy
// X-DNS-Prefetch-Control
// ...and more
```

---

### 🟠 MEDIUM — A05: Security Misconfiguration — No Rate Limiting

**Issue:** There are no rate limits on any endpoint. This enables brute-force attacks, credential stuffing (on future auth endpoints), and denial-of-service via request floods.

**Fix:**

```bash
