### 🟡 MEDIUM — No CORS Policy

Express serves requests from any origin by default. Without explicit CORS configuration, browsers may be tricked into making cross-origin requests on behalf of authenticated users.

**Fix:**

```js
const cors = require('cors');

app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourdomain.com'],   // allowlist specific origins
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization'],
  credentials: true,
}));
```

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — No Global Error Handler (Stack Trace Leakage)

Without a centralized error handler, unhandled exceptions may surface raw stack traces to clients, leaking implementation details (OWASP A05).

**Fix:** Add an error-handling middleware as the last `app.use()`:

```js
// Must be defined AFTER all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // Log internally
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({
    error: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'
      ? 'Internal Server Error'
