Port `3000` is hardcoded and the app listens on plain HTTP only.

**Fix:**

```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```

In production, terminate TLS at the load balancer or reverse proxy (nginx, AWS ALB), and redirect HTTP → HTTPS. If running standalone:

```js
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');
https.createServer({
  key: fs.readFileSync(process.env.TLS_KEY_PATH),
  cert: fs.readFileSync(process.env.TLS_CERT_PATH),
}, app).listen(443);
```

